---

<Layout title="About">
  <Container>
    <Sectionhead>
      <Fragment slot="title">About</Fragment>
      <Fragment slot="desc">
        Download free geometric patterns for coloring
      </Fragment>
    </Sectionhead>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 mx-auto max-w-4xl mt-16">
      <h2 class="font-bold text-3xl text-gray-800">
        What is PatternBloom?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-500">
        PatternBloom is a creative haven for anyone who loves the relaxing art of coloring. Here, you’ll find a growing collection of ready-to-print black-and-white geometric patterns, each designed to inspire creativity, promote mindfulness, and bring a sense of calm to your day
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 mx-auto max-w-4xl mt-16">
      <h2 class="font-bold text-3xl text-gray-800">
        How the Patterns Are Made
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-500">
        All the patterns on this patterns are created using generative art, primarily with the p5.js library. Generative art involves writing code to generate designs using mathematical rules, randomness, and algorithms. Unlike AI, which uses machine learning to analyze and replicate existing styles or patterns, generative art is rooted in the direct control of the artist, blending logic and creativity to produce unique, intentional designs.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-500">
        This approach allows for infinite possibilities while ensuring every pattern is thoughtfully crafted to be enjoyable and engaging for coloring.
    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 mx-auto max-w-4xl mt-16">
      <h2 class="font-bold text-3xl text-gray-800">
        About the Author
      </h2>
      <div class="py-6 md:order-1 hidden md:block max-w-xs">
        <Picture
          src={profileImage}
          alt="Profile Image"
          widths={[200, 400, 600]}
          loading="eager"
          format="avif"
        />
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-500">
        This patterns is the side project of Elena Torró, a software engineer from Murcia, Spain, who is passionate about generative art, open source, and exploring the fascinating intersection of art and technology. Through this patterns, Elena combines her technical expertise and artistic curiosity to share designs that inspire relaxation and creativity.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-500">
        Thank you for visiting, and happy coloring!
      </p>
    </div>

